Sentencas: Series compounds Ca-3(Co0.9M0.1)(2)O-6 (M=Co, Fe, Mn, Ni) with hexagonal crystal structure were prepared by sol-gel route as the cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Evaluation of Ca3(Co,M)2O6 (M = Co, Fe, Mn, Ni) as new cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Effects of the varied atomic compositions on the structure, electrical conductivity, thermal expansion and electrochemical performance were systematically evaluated.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ca3(Co,M)2O6 (M = Co, Fe, Mn, Ni) as new cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Experimental results showed that the lattice parameters of Ca-3(Co0.9M0.1)(2)O-6 and Ca-3(Co0.9M0.1)(2)O-6 were both expanded to certain degree.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ca3(Co,M)2O6 (M = Co, Fe, Mn, Ni) as new cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electron-doping and hole-doping effects were expected in Ca-3(Co0.9M0.1)(2)O-6 and Ca-3(Co0.9M0.1)(2)O-6 respectively according to the chemical states of constituent elements and thermal-activated behavior of electrical conductivity.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ca3(Co,M)2O6 (M = Co, Fe, Mn, Ni) as new cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thermal expansion coefficients (TEC) of Ca-3(Co0.9M0.1)(2)O-6 were measured to be distributed around 16 x 10(-6) K-1, and compositional elements of Fe, Mn, and Ni were especially beneficial for alleviation of the thermal expansion problem of cathode materials.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ca3(Co,M)2O6 (M = Co, Fe, Mn, Ni) as new cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: By using Ca-3(Co0.9M0.1)(2)O-6 as the cathodes operated at 800 degrees C, the interfacial area-specific resistance varied in the order of M=Co < M=Fe < M=Ni < M=Mn, and the over-potential increased in the order of M=Fe approximate to M=Co < M=Mn < M=Ni.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ca3(Co,M)2O6 (M = Co, Fe, Mn, Ni) as new cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Among all of these compounds, Ca-3(Co0.9M0.1)(2)O-6 showed the best electrochemical performance and the power density as high as ca.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ca3(Co,M)2O6 (M = Co, Fe, Mn, Ni) as new cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: 500 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C achieved in the single cell with La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.83Mg0.17O2.815 as electrolyte and Ni-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 as anode.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ca3(Co,M)2O6 (M = Co, Fe, Mn, Ni) as new cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ca-3(Co0.9M0.1)(2)O-6 (M=Co, Fe, Mn, Ni) can be used as the cost-effective cathode materials for SOFCs.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ca3(Co,M)2O6 (M = Co, Fe, Mn, Ni) as new cathode materials for solid-oxide fuel cells
